wiki.summary: “I Don’t Care” is an upbeat collaboration between pop stars Ed Sheeran and Justin Bieber. Both singers use this track to describe being at a party, but wanting to leave due to feeling lonely or having social anxiety. That special someone by their side saves the day and makes them feel less alone in the end. The duo had previously worked together on Purpose single, “Love Yourself” and “Cold Water.” Read more on Last.fm.
